channel.title: RFD minigame save problem
channel.description:
Okey so my rfd minigame doesn't save atm. Once u relog u have to start over the minigame from wave 0. Any1 knows where the saving part is happening? Or why it wouldn't save? Let me know what files u wanna have a look at.
This is the dropbox link for the playersave.java : https://dl.dropbox.com/s/smgwbuxdxo7778y/PlayerSave%20-%20kopie.java

item.title: RFD minigame save problem
item.dc:creator: @iisayboom iisayboom
item.description:
@iisayboom wrote:

[quote=“Zymus, post:10, topic:550605”][quote author=iisayboom link=topic=669515.msg4477023#msg4477023 date=1426541408]

Okey so my rfd minigame doesn’t save atm. Once u relog u have to start over the minigame from wave 0. Any1 knows where the saving part is happening? Or why it wouldn’t save? Let me know what files u wanna have a look at.

You’ll have to show us your player save/load mechanics.

KK ive added the dropbox link to the playersave.java

For one, that’s not a valid java class name. No spaces, no hyphens. I’m looking at the contents right now. Also, in the future, uploading it to something like pastie or pastebin would be easier.

Aight ill keep that in mind to put it on pastebin or w.e. uhh, what do you mean with a valid java class name, whats a correct one then?
Also if u wanna explain it decent to me add me on skype : nielskeeeeeeeen , u can also teamview me if you want.

As in the name of the class is PlayerSave, but you saved it as PlayerSave - kopie.java; Java is very specific about it’s convention in this aspect. Also, the reason it’s not saving, is because you haven’t told it to save it; at least not in the file that you posted. Do you have a PlayerSave.java file?

Thats was the PlayerSave.java, but i copied it and uploaded it. Bit thats the normal Playersave.java

Okay then that’s why it’s not working. I couldn’t find any keys in the file dealing with rfd.

Could you maybe help me out how to fix it? Like help my by teamviewer or skype? I’m in some serious need of help…
[/quote]

Sorry, but no. I’m sure if you did a search in the tutorials section, there would probably be something about adding fields to the player save.[/quote]

Yeh i’ve fixed it
